Just sad state.

### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

I am writing a component that needs to listen for changes to the input property. Since I am using signals, I tried using effect, but I found that the effect was not called when the input property changed.

**I found that if I call the signal in the effect, everything works fine.**

```javascript
effect(() => {
  // this.id();
  untracked(() => {
    console.log(this.id());
  });
});
```

### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

https://stackblitz.com/edit/sqh7rz?file=src%2Fmain.ts

### Please provide the exception or error you saw

```true
The effect was not called when the input property changed.
```


